
1.ECMAScript 2015 (or ES6) is the sixth and major edition of the ECMAScript language specification standard. 
2.It defines the standard for the JavaScript implementation.
3.ES6 brought significant changes to the JavaScript language. 
4.It introduces several new features such as, block-scoped variables, new loop for iterating over arrays and objects, template literals, and many other enhancements to make JavaScript programming easier and more fun.
5.Examples
i. let keyword
ii.const keyword.
iii.Arrow Functions.
iv.For/of.
v.Map Objects.
vi.Set Objects.
vii.Classes.
viii.Promises.
and many more
